At 02:10 PM 5/15/2002 -0500, Jako wrote:
>  I made a pressure brake bleeder from a one gallon garden sprayer
>for about 10 bucks. If you drill a hole in the top near the shoulder
>you can install a threaded tire valve stem so that you can charge it
>with your air compressor. Then you can have so much pressure
>that when the m.c. cap fails, you can rapidly coat your interior
>with brake fluid!

Which is why the Motive Products bleeder has a pressure gauge attached.

>(maybe the hand pump would have been good enough!)

I'm sure it would.  I run mine between ten and fifteen PSI.
Just make SURE that master cylinder cap is screwed on properly and
tightly!  My neighbors certainly got to hear some colorful language, while
out working in their yard, last weekend.

